== Way of Abiding: Everything arises, manifest, and are freed within awareness #text(fill: gray)[(Cmt)] 

Cmt on *The Precious Treasury of the Way of Abiding*, #46  

Dawai's commentary on Root Verses and Auto-commentary 
Samaya — The Theme of Openness / pp. 159-161

Dawai: Dzogchen is exceptional because with the pointing-out instructions, which ideally should come first, teachers—Lamas, Rinpoches, Geshes, Khenpos, whoever—they will typically evaluate a practitioner and say, "Oh, you are not ready for the pointing-out," or, "You are ready for the pointing-out." So then they will prescribe, essentially, some practices: "You are stealing too much. You are lying too much. Go take some vows, right, to get your mind right." So you stop feeling like a jerk all the time, and then maybe you will see awareness.

